From b3cdfdf3c252f3b6b2ff59ae8095cccbc8db00ec Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: zihaofu245 <172541422+ZihaoFU245@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Apr 2026 15:33:32 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] Allow HTTP CONNECT method passthrough

This commit allows h2/h3 connect method to passthrough
nginx internal request parsing. Modules can then
handle CONNECT method by setting allow_connect
bit field to 1.

The logic still aligns with HTTP/1.1, allow_connect
is always checked first, 405 will return before 400
(Header parsing)
