From 35d1f7f61ea5d1e7dcb468d7ae64346894b2b2bb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: zihaofu245 <172541422+ZihaoFU245@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 16:53:57 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] Allow Extended CONNECT to pass header parsing

For classic connect method, it does not contain
:path nor :scheme, so set it to "/" for nginx core
to continue parsing.

For extended connect, there are :path, :scheme,
:path and :protocol. If scheme and path is provided,
then set it to value in the icoming headers.
:protocol header is not in nginx core. It is still
not handled
---
